works.description: One of the rarest editions of Mein Kampf signed by Adolf Hitler will be up for auction later this month at Mullock’s, and it’s expected to sell for as much as £30,000 (US $48,880). The Nazi dictator wrote this particular Mein Kampf when he was in Landsberg prison in Germany in 1925. Expert Richard Westwood Brookes of Mullocks auctioneers in Shropshire said that this is probably the rarest ever edition of Mein Kampf ever to be offered at auction.
